description:
Xubuntu 14.10 * Zorin Lite 9 * Peppermint 5 * LXDE Puppy * Simplicity * Porteus * AVG

SliTaz * TinyCore * OpenElec XBMC * Hirens * FreeDOS * AndroidX86 * Partition Wizard


Are you ready to try the best modern lightweight Linux distros and rescue tools? The 2015 Lite-Speed collection contains our top selections from well designed, feature rich, lightweight and fast Linux distros and tools. Linux stars range from ultra-tiny TinyCore (15MB) and SliTaz (44MB) to the very popular Xubuntu (1GB).

All distros can either be run &quot;live&quot; direct from USB or installed to your hard disk. A major new feature is that almost all distros now have USB &quot;persistence&quot; (see important persistence information). 2.4GB of USB persistence files were pre-installed to save settings, etc. once you logout from a USB &quot;live&quot; session.

---

Note: this download uses PendriveLinux YUMI to create the basic bootable USB file structure. From the Click-START (or Click-START-WinXP) menu, you will use YUMI only once to format the USB flash drive and install &quot;Try Unlisted ISO (Grub)&quot; a single file empty.iso on the USB drive. After that, you will not need to use YUMI again. The real Linux and Tools distros will be installed on USB from the Click-START menu using Lite-S1.exe and Lite-S2.exe self-extracting files.[/color]

